Ad Text:
Position overview

Ongoing, full-time position based at Mipac’s Brisbane head office, with international and domestic travel opportunities.
Competitive salary commensurate with experience, plus additional uplift when working at site

The opportunity

You hold a degree in engineering or computer science and have a strong background in data historians, particularly the AVEVA PI System. In this role, you’ll support clients by implementing and optimising historian systems, integrating process control technologies, and delivering technical solutions that improve operational performance and decision-making. You’ll also lead and deliver integration projects that enhance data visibility and operational outcomes for clients across global sites.

In this role, your responsibilities will include:

Supporting clients with their ongoing operations by maintaining and optimising their data historians
Assisting clients with the set up of new historian systems which includes design procurement, installation, configuration, testing, tuning, training and support
Reviewing and auditing data historian deployments
Providing sound engineering and analysis techniques to understand client needs and utilising relevant tools/methodologies to identify solutions
Undertaking and coordinating integration projects in Australia and overseas that enhance clients' useful performance data availability and decision-making capability
Conducting engineering investigations, designing and calculating, preparing engineering documentation, and applying sound engineering practices to achieve objectives of quality, schedule, and budgeted hours
Providing technical advice and assistance to other team members
Evaluating new technologies and methods for future applications
Developing and maintaining a full working knowledge of Mipac and partner software used in delivering Digital Solutions Implementation integrations

 About you; ideally, you will have:

A degree in Engineering (metallurgy, process, chemical, mechatronic, electrical), Computer Science, or another relevant tertiary qualification
Extensive industry experience with historians, specializing in the AVEVA/OSIsoft PI System and PI Asset Framework development
Proficiency in integrating data from process control systems and other data sources, as well as managing installation, configuration, validation, tuning, historians and downtime systems
Skills in SQL queries, scripting, and process analysis for report creation using historian data
A strong understanding of Windows OS, networking, and system security
Experience in the energy and resources sector is an advantage
Willingness to travel to sites (domestically and internationally) occasionally as required
Demonstrated strong interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively across teams and stakeholders
Proven capability in writing technical documentation and scopes of work.

Benefits

At Mipac, we see our people as our most valuable asset and are committed to ensuring our staff feel safe, secure and comfortable, are given continuous learning opportunities and feel valued. That’s why we offer:

Competitive salaries with an annual bonus payment.
An opportunity to work on interesting and diverse projects nationally and internationally.
Continuous learning and professional development opportunities, including free access to LinkedIn Learning.
Support to gain further accreditation and certifications through our Study Support policy.
Health & wellbeing benefits including private health discounts and access to an Employee Assistance Program (EAP).
Free onsite parking (conditions apply - of up to 2 days per week) and end-of-trip facilities in Brisbane CBD.
Access to Novated leasing and an employee benefits platform to access discounted gift cards etc.

About us

Would you like to work for a global company that’s on a trajectory of sustained growth? Are you looking for a work environment in which diversity and inclusivity are celebrated?

At Mipac, we’re global leaders in operational technology, control systems and engineering services across a range of sectors. We empower and engage workforces, creating automation and digitalisation solutions for our clients which enable easy decision-making and increased productivity, performance and safety. We believe every problem has a solution and are dedicated to solving even the most complex of challenges.

For more about what we do, visit www.mipac.com.au.

Does this sound like you?

If this opportunity sounds right for you, please apply today.

Please note: Applicants must have full working rights in Australia.

Not the right opportunity for you right now, but you'd still like to work for Mipac? Visit www.mipac.com.au careers section to see what other vacancies for which we are currently recruiting. Here you can also submit an expression of interest application so that you can be considered for other opportunities.

Senior AI Engineer

Full-Time | Permanent

We’re working with a well-established insurance company that’s embracing Generative AI and LLMs to transform how they operate—and they’re building a seriously talented team to do it.

They’re looking for a Senior AI Engineer who’s hands-on, creative, and excited to take ownership of real-world GenAI solutions. You won’t just be tweaking models—you’ll be designing and delivering production-grade systems from scratch, with the autonomy to experiment, lead, and build.

Our client has an office in Sydney but are open to candidates in all parts of Australia. 

Why You’ll Love This Role – the Benefits

12.5% performance bonus – real recognition for the impact you make
$600 annual wellbeing allowance – spend it on your gym, sports, or whatever keeps you sharp.
Birthday leave – take the day off on us.
Volunteer leave – paid day to give back to causes you care about.
CEO Sleepout participation – be part of meaningful social impact.
Ongoing L&D – funded learning opportunities and internal mobility
Creative freedom – you’ll have the license to innovate, challenge ideas, and own your solutions
No rigid boxes – grow your role, shape the team, and explore new tools and approaches
Supportive, agile culture – work alongside forward-thinking engineers and product leaders.

What You’ll Do

Design, develop, and deploy machine learning and GenAI systems for key business use cases.
Apply and fine-tune LLMs (OpenAI, Claude, Cohere, LLaMA, etc.), build prompt pipelines and embedding-based search.
Develop retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems and deploy models into production.
Collaborate with product, engineering, and data teams to deliver outcomes—not just models.
Build scalable AI systems with a focus on maintainability, performance, and responsible use.

What You’ll Bring

4–6+ years in ML or software engineering, with 2+ years in GenAI / LLMs.
Strong Python skills and ML ecosystem experience.
Background in RAG, prompt engineering, vector search, or model fine-tuning.
Experience with MLOps / LLMOps and cloud tools (especially AWS – Bedrock, SageMaker).
A builder’s mindset—creative, curious, and comfortable getting hands dirty.

If you’re looking for more than just another AI role—and want to join a team where your ideas, input, and ownership actually matter—this is it.

Apply now or reach out to liamc@therecruitmentcompany.com for a confidential chat.

Welcome to MVSI!

We are a dynamic team of 70+ professionals, spread across the Globe with offices in Australia, EMEA, the US and the Philippines. Our innovative SaaS product is trusted by banks, Fintech’s, and crypto services worldwide to manage their AML/KYC Compliance requirements. We have always harnessed the power of cutting-edge technology and are currently exploring the exciting realm of LLM (think ChatGPT) to further elevate our offerings. Our company culture is built on a foundation of support and commitment to career development. 

 

We truly value our people and invite you to join us to experience all that we have to offer!

Why Apply?

Get an awesome career! Ours is a specialised industry, and experience is in short supply. We employ people from all walks of life and train them to be certified professionals over time. This is a fabulous opportunity to find a new direction, build transferable skills, and enjoy a profession where every day is interesting, and you'll want to come to work.

Job Summary

The ideal candidate will have strong analytical skills, a deep understand of testing methodologies, and experience working in Agile environments. You will be responsible for designing and implementing testing strategies, ensuring the quality of complex software systems, and collaborating with cross-

Next Steps

If this sounds like you, and you want a great career opportunity, we would love to hear from you. Ready for immediate start, reach out with your CV's and we will be in touch!

The clients we work with share our values.

Job Title: Senior AI / Full Stack Engineer (LLMs, RAG, Vector DBs, Agentic AI) - 12m FTC
Ad Text:
Our client is on the lookout for a Senior Full Stack AI Engineer who loves solving complex problems and building intelligent systems end-to-end.

You’ll be part of a small, high-impact engineering team working at the forefront of AI product development, applying LLMs, RAG pipelines, vector databases, and agentic AI.

If you’re hands-on, product-minded, and excited about pushing the limits of what AI systems can do — this one’s for you.

What You’ll Be Doing

Designing and building scalable backend systems in Python (FastAPI, Flask, Django).
Developing clean APIs and end-to-end data pipelines.
Building modern front-end interfaces (React, TypeScript).
Integrating and deploying AI/LLM systems into production environments.
Implementing retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) workflows and vector search (e.g. Pinecone, Weaviate, FAISS).
Working with autonomous / agentic AI systems, enabling them to reason, plan, and take action.
Collaborating closely with product and research teams to deliver practical, production-grade AI tools.

Tech Stack & Skills
You don’t need to tick every box, but you’ll likely have experience with most of these:

Python, SQL/PostgreSQL, TypeScript, React
Vector databases (Weaviate, Pinecone, FAISS)
LLMs – fine-tuning, prompt engineering, and API integration
RAG pipelines and hybrid retrieval architectures
LangChain, LlamaIndex, or similar frameworks
Agentic AI systems or multi-agent orchestration
Cloud deployment (AWS / GCP / Azure)

What We’re Looking For

5+ years of software engineering experience
Solid understanding of both backend systems and AI applications
Proven ability to deliver end-to-end production systems
A passion for experimentation, iteration, and working with emerging AI technologies
Strong communication and collaboration skills
Why You’ll Love It

Work on cutting-edge AI projects with real impact
Small, high-performing engineering team – no bureaucracy, just impact
Flexibility and autonomy to shape your work
Competitive salary and genuine technical ownership
Sound like you?

If you’re excited by the idea of designing and deploying intelligent, LLM-driven systems — we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now or reach out for a confidential chat.

Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth, Adelaide and Auckland. But you have choice in where and how you work, we trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

Job Description


What you’d be doing in this role:
As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.

At the moment, this role is focused on:

Defining and delivering the long-term AI platform strategy, aligning technical direction with Canva’s broader product and AI research vision.
Defining and delivering the next-generation AI platform, transforming how AI is developed, evaluated, and deployed at global scale.
Partnering with leaders across Engineering, Product, and Data to ensure AI enablement across Canva’s ecosystem.
Coaching and developing a diverse team of engineering leads and senior engineers across our global workforce to achieve technical excellence at scale.
Ensuring the AI Platform remains reliable, secure, and performant while enabling rapid innovation.
Acting as a visible champion for AI and platform excellence across Canva and the wider engineering community.

You're probably a match if

You’re a platform believer and technical innovator at heart, driven to lead and expand foundational AI capabilities at scale that redefine what’s possible.

You’ve successfully led large-scale engineering or platform teams in AI/ML, data, or infrastructure domains.

You have deep technical expertise in modern AI platforms, distributed systems, or cloud-native architectures.

You anticipate challenges before they arise and bring clarity and direction to complex, cross-functional problems.

You’re known for visible, forward-leaning leadership — shaping direction early and rallying people behind shared goals.

You balance autonomy with visibility — managing up and across senior leadership confidently and transparently.

You build cultures of accountability, empowerment, and support, where teams thrive on trust and ownership.

About the team
At Canva, we empower everyone to design, using technology to simplify challenges and enhance the enjoyable parts of the design process. Our Generative AI (GenAI) supergroup exists to make Canva feel less like a tool, but more like a creative partner that wows - an AI collaborator that understands your intent, amplifies your ideas, and helps the world create with joy. You can see our recent launches in canva.com/magic.

The AI Platform Group is a key part of Canva’s Generative AI Supergroup and broader AI ecosystem, laying the technical foundation for Canva’s next wave of transformative AI experience. From massively scalable model serving infrastructure to next-generation training and evaluation platforms, we enable thousands of engineers and product teams to create innovative, responsible, and reliable AI features used by millions around the world.

What's in it for you?    

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too

Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers

An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more

Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Job Title: Machine Learning Engineer - Data - AI Research
Ad Text:
Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora,你好, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point. 

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney, with a second campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth, Adelaide, and Auckland, NZ. You have flexibility in how and where you work — whether that's from one of our spaces, from home, or a mix of both. This role is remote-friendly within Australia or New Zealand, so you can choose the setup that empowers you and your team to do your best work.

Job Description


About the Role

As a Research MLE at Canva, you'll be responsible for high-performance data acquisition, processing, and annotation to enable the training of cutting-edge models. Your focus will be on sourcing data, automation, building performant infrastructure for filtering and analyzing, and dealing with petabyte-scale data. You'll be the crucial link that makes novel model development, training, and evaluation possible, accelerating Canva's cutting-edge research.

Key Focus Areas

Data Acquisition: Developing scalable tools and pipelines for acquiring diverse datasets from multiple sources
Curation: Engineering robust solutions for filtering, deduplication, quality assessment, and curating data that meets specific research requirements and model training criteria
Data Infrastructure: Developing high-throughput tools for interfacing with large-scale data pools, enabling efficient querying, sampling, and extracting valuable statistical insights and patterns

Primary Responsibilities

Work alongside research teams to ensure continuous flow of high-quality data toward active projects, understanding their specific dataset requirements and delivery timelines
Curate targeted subsets of data using ML techniques including clustering, embedding-based similarity search, and automated quality scoring
Extract, visualize, and communicate actionable insights about dataset composition, distributions, biases, and statistical properties to inform research decisions
Build performant, parallel algorithms for gathering and processing data at scale, optimizing for both throughput and cost-efficiency across distributed systems
Engineer intuitive interfaces and tooling to help researchers explore, sample, and interact with large datasets without requiring deep infrastructure knowledge
Work with paired multimodal data (text-image, audio-video, etc.), ensuring alignment quality, handling synchronization challenges, and maintaining multimodal correspondence
Leverage high-performance parallel computing frameworks (Ray, Spark, torch.distributed, DeepSpeed, etc) and cloud infrastructure for distributed data operations on petabyte-scale datasets

You’re probably a match if you have:

A strong aesthetic sense, with a background or demonstrated passion for visual design or human-computer interaction.

Strong proficiency in Python and ML frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow).

Extensive experience with designing and implementing large-scale data processing workflows using libraries like Pandas and data warehousing solutions such as Snowflake.

Solid understanding of statistical methods, including experimental design, A/B testing, and quality evaluation systems.

Experience with generative AI and synthetic data generation is highly desirable.

Nice to have:

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure) for data storage, processing, and MLOps related to dataset management.

Experience with MLOps practices and tools specifically for data versioning, lineage, and pipeline automation.

Ability to develop data visualization or data collection interfaces (e.g., TypeScript, Python).

Additional Information


Don't tick all the boxes? Don't worry about that - nobody does!  We’d still love to hear from you! At Canva, we know that great engineers come from a variety of backgrounds, and we value passion, curiosity, and a willingness to learn just as much as specific experience. If you're excited about this role but don’t tick every box, we encourage you to apply, you might a great fit in ways you didn’t expect!

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out  lifeatcanva.com  for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.
